More than sixty illegal miners were arrested on Thursday during Operation O Kae Molao. Gauteng police spokesperson Captain Mavela Masondo said they also arrested two suspects believed to be supporting illegal miners with equipment. “These suspects allegedly offered the police thousands of rands for the release of suspects arrested for illegal mining in Roodepoort today,” he said. Masondo said the suspects are expected to appear at Roodepoort Magistrate's Court tomorrow facing charges of bribery amongst other crimes. ALSO READ: MZANSI'S COVID-19 DEATH TOLL JUMPS TO 48 Gauteng Provincial Commissioner, General Elias Mawela, commended the police for the arrest. "We have been hunting for the people that are leading this scourge of illegal mining in our province. I believe the arrests of these suspects will help us trace others who are still at large,” Mawela said in a statement. Meanwhile, Masondo said they arrested 556 suspects that have been on the run for committing serious ranging from rape, armed robbery, house robbery, business robbery, attempted murder, assault, car hijacking and sexual assault. All the arrested suspects are expected to appear at various magistrates’ courts from tomorrow.